## Policy Implications

Distribution analysis reveals whether headline averages mask structural inequality. A {{ "high" if cv is defined and cv is not none and cv > 0.5 else "moderate" }} spread in {{ metric_name }} means that policy interventions calibrated to the national average will systematically under-serve the most deprived areas. BSIP funding allocations should account for this variation by using distributional metrics (e.g., 25th percentile performance) as targets rather than mean performance.

